article.headline: North Dakota 74, Chicago St. 52
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Troy Huff scored 21 points and Patrick Mitchell scored 20 to lead North Dakota past Chicago State 74-52 on Monday night. Jamal Webb added 14 points and seven assists for North Dakota (14-14, 6-4 Great West), playing its final home game of the season. Mitchell had eight rebounds and Huff seven as the Fighting Sioux owned a 43-31 advantage on the boards. North Dakota used an 11-0 run late in the first half to open a 29-20 lead at the break, then led by as many as 25 points in the second half. Christian Wall led Chicago State (6-24, 3-8) with 27 points and Carl Montgomery had 13 points.
